ANTHRAX, HUMAN, BOVINE - KYRGYZSTAN (JALALABAD)
***********************************************

A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: 16 Jun 2011
Source: 24.kg News Agency [edited]
http://eng.24.kg/community/2011/06/16/18733.html


2 persons take (have) anthrax in Jalal-Abad province, S. Kyrgyzstan
-------------------------------------------------------------------
2 persons in Jalal-Abad province are suspected to (have) anthrax,
according to the press-service of the Emergency Situations Ministry.

Reportedly, on 6 Jun 2011 one of farmers distributed the meat of the
cattle with assent of the local animal doctor at Kolmon pasture. To
date the number of people [who] consumed the meat is being
established. The meat was sent for examination to the
sanitary-epidemiological inspection service in Jalal-Abad city while
assays of the infected persons are sent to the [public health]
laboratory in Osh city.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[An all too common occurrence in Southern Kyrgyzstan. The problem is
that this bovine disease is not controlled in the bordering Uzbek
province and the 2 provinces weak control programmes (Jala Abad and
Osh) create a setting that feeds off of each others weaknesses.

To find Jalal-Abad, go to:
http://www.fallingrain.com/world/KG/03/JalalAbad.html.

[For a map demonstrating the proximity of Jala Abad, Osh and
Uzbekistan bordering areas see
http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/kyrgyzstan_rel96.jpg. -
Mods.MHJ/MPP]]
